        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 2:02PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 201 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Abbeville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hodges, Donalds, Abbeville, Shoals Junction, Cokesbury, Due West,
Ware Shoals, and Lake Greenwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
